Question: How to create a notification in Android?:
Answer:<<<api>>>: android.app.NotificationManager
<<<code>>>: NotificationManager notificationManager = (NotificationManager) getSystemService(Context.NOTIFICATION_SERVICE);
Notification notification = new Notification.Builder(this)
    .setContentTitle("My notification")
    .setContentText("This is my notification")
    .setSmallIcon(R.drawable.icon)
    .build();
notificationManager.notify(1, notification);
<<<explanation>>>: Use the NotificationManager class to create a notification. The Notification.Builder class is used to build the notification. The setContentTitle and setContentText methods are used to set the title and text of the notification, and the setSmallIcon method is used to set the small icon of the notification. The build method is used to create the notification. The notify method is used to post the notification.
